        {{> components/c002-image-content-cta
                id=''
                class=""
                heading-primary='Training and taper plan'
                heading-secondary='Making the most of the time off'
                body-content='
                <p>As this became a short term target of mine I stopped with all the swim training as I only need run and bike. In terms of training i managed to get in a good number of speed sessions for running and for the bike I got in a lot of virtual training sessions at the gym, over the course of a couple of weeks I have gone from speed training at 15kmph to 16kmph and taken my average watts over an hour on the bike from 160ish to 180ish.</p>
                <h6>Penultimate week - intense (around 14hrs of training)</h6>
                <ul class="">
                    <li class="">2hrs on watt bike + Speed training</li>
                    <li class="">1.5hrs on watt bike + LISS cardio * 2</li>
                    <li class="">1hrs on watt bike + Speed training * 3 </li>
                </ul>
                <h6>Final week - taper (around 7hrs of training)</h6>
                <ul class="">
                    <li class="">Ashridge bike route x 4 loops + 10km run on the treadmill</li>
                    <li class="">Ashridge bike route x 3 loops + 7.5km run on the treadmill</li>
                    <li class="">Ashridge bike route x 2 loops + 5km run on the treadmill</li>
                    <li class="">Do nothing up to the event</li>
                </ul>
                <p><i class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle text-danger" aria-hidden="true"></i> During the final week into the event on what was supposed to be a medium pace 4 loops of the Ashridge route I fell off my bike quite badly and injured nearly every part of the right hand side of my body (see&nbsp;<a href="http://localhost:3000/pages-handled/app/triathlon-ashridge.html#injuries">injury list</a>), this meant I couldn`t finish my training plan completely but worst of all I now have the `fear`, I worry i may end up holding back on the day at certain points on the bike due the accident</p>
            '
        }}

        {{> components/c002-image-content-cta
                id=''
                class=""
                heading-primary='Nutrition on the day and beforehand'
                heading-secondary='Trying to stop the legs feeling like jelly'
                body-content='
                <p>Having done the event before I found that after the 10km run and start of the bike my legs felt heavy, I think the issue was i didn`t take any calories with my on the run so my legs were slightly depleted once I jumped on, this time I will be taking a sports drink to sip on every 2.5km lap, on the bike I will have another sports drink and will use every 5km and also an energy gel to take right at the very start. For the final 5km, I will take the same bottle from the 10km to hydrate around the last 2 laps. I will start the day with a big bowl of porridge.</p>
                <ul class="list-inline">
                    <li class="list-inline-item">Porridge</li>
                    <li class="list-inline-item">2 x Lucozade drinks</li>
                    <li class="list-inline-item">1 x energy gel</li>
                </ul>
            '
        }}

        {{> components/c002-image-content-cta
