        {{> components/c002-image-content-cta
                id=''
                class=""
                heading-primary='How it went on the day'
                heading-secondary='Reality check'
                body-content='
                <p>Got to the event bright and early and you could tell straight away it was much more serious than the previous time I entered, not only was it a BTU Qualifier event it was also a Triathlon England Championship, which meant there were a lot of very good athletes there.</p>
                <p>Overall I came in about 5 minutes quicker which I was very pleased with, improving on each element except for the initial 10km run where I lost around 40 seconds of time. My bike loops were around 23.5 minutes each (compared to 24.75 minutes previously) and my final 5km which felt a lot easier than before was just over 30 seconds faster. I also managed to claw back around 30 seconds in time from the transitions.</p>
                '
        }}

